I just saw this now, sorry for being 5 days late if you even end up noticing it.<p>The typing is governed by YAML standards. This is why symbols are left out. Since it uses `YAML.dump` and `YAML.load` with the set/get, it will automatically assume the string &#x27;1&#x27; is an integer, &#x27;1.0&#x27; a float, and so on.<p>> is it possible to enumerate the versions of key-values that have been saved?<p>Yes, using the `get_version` method, you could do something like:<p><pre><code>    all_items = $ITEMS[key].map { |hash| db.get(hash) }
</code></pre>
